{"title_page": "Quenton Nelson", "text_new": "{{short description|American football offensive guard}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name                = Quenton Nelson\n| image               = Quenton Nelson.png\n| image_size          = \n| alt                 = \n| caption             = Nelson at the [[2020 Pro Bowl]]\n| current_team        = Indianapolis Colts\n| number              = 56\n| position            = [[Guard (American and Canadian football)|Offensive guard]]\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1996|3|19}}\n| birth_place         = [[Holmdel Township, New Jersey|Holmdel, New Jersey]]\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| height_ft           = 6\n| height_in           = 5\n| weight_lb           = 330\n| high_school         = [[Red Bank Catholic High School|Red Bank Catholic]]<br>([[Red Bank, New Jersey]])\n| college             = [[Notre Dame Fighting Irish football|Notre Dame]]\n| draftyear           = 2018\n| draftround          = 1\n| draftpick           = 6\n| pastteams           = \n* [[Indianapolis Colts]] ({{NFL Year|2018}}\u2013present)\n| status              = Active\n| highlights          =\n* 2\u00d7 [[Pro Bowl]] ([[2019 Pro Bowl|2018]], [[2020 Pro Bowl|2019]])\n* 2\u00d7 First-team [[All-Pro]] ([[2018 All-Pro Team|2018]], [[2019 All-Pro Team|2019]])\n* [[PFWA All-Rookie Team]] ([[PFWA All-Rookie Team#2018|2018]])\n* Unanimous [[All-America]]n ([[2017 College Football All-America Team|2017]])\n* ''[[USA Today]]'' High School All-American ([[2013 USA Today All-USA high school football team|2013]])\n| statleague          = NFL\n| statseason          = 2019\n| statweek            =\n| statlabel1          = Games played\n| statvalue1          = 32\n| statlabel2          = Games started\n| statvalue2          = 32\n| nflnew              = quentonnelson/2560820\n}}\n\n'''Quenton Emerson Nelson''' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S9Jf0HLy1r4|title=Colts Quenton Nelson On Why 17 NFL Games is a Bad Idea & Growing Up Big|last=Nelson|first=Quenton|date=4/10/2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>(born March 19, 1996) is an [[American football]] [[Guard (American and Canadian football)|offensive guard]] for the [[Indianapolis Colts]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL). He played [[college football]] at [[Notre Dame Fighting Irish football|Notre Dame]] and was drafted by the Colts in the first round (sixth overall) of the [[2018 NFL Draft]]. In his first two seasons in the league, Nelson was named a first-team [[All-Pro]] selection and voted to the [[Pro Bowl]].\n\n==Early years==\nNelson is the youngest of four children of Craig and Maryellen Nelson, in which she noted Quenton to be a large baby at birth (10lb 10 oz or 4.82kg).<ref>{{Citation |title=Quenton Nelson: The Left Guard YOU Should be Talking About {{!}} NFL Films Presents |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FafC8RvD3b8 |language=en |access-date=December 13, 2019}}</ref> He grew up in [[Holmdel Township, New Jersey]] and attended [[Holmdel High School]] as a freshman before transferring to [[Red Bank Catholic High School]] in [[Red Bank, New Jersey]], where he was an All-Star in basketball as a power forward/center.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nj.com/hssports/blog/football/index.ssf/2013/05/quenton_nelson_of_red_bank_catholic_commits_to_notre_dame.html |title=Notre Dame lands commitment from Quenton Nelson of Red Bank Catholic |last=Lanni |first=Patrick |date=May 2, 2013 |website=[[The Star-Ledger]] |access-date=November 18, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.app.com/story/sports/nfl/2018/04/26/nfl-draft-quenton-nelson-first-round/555608002/ |title=NFL Draft: Colts select Holmdel's Quenton Nelson No. 6 overall |last=Edelson |first=Nelson |date=April 26, 2018 |website=[[Asbury Park Press]] |access-date=August 20, 2018}}</ref> He committed to the [[University of Notre Dame]] to play college football.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2013-05-02/sports/chi-notre-dame-football-quenton-nelson-commits-20130502_1_twitter-account-top-lineman-latest-recruiting-haul |title=Notre Dame football: Quenton Nelson commits |last=Hamilton |first=Brian |date=May 2, 2013 |website=Chicago Tribune |access-date=April 24, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/blog/notre-dame-football/post/_/id/15205/nelson-becomes-no-9-for-2014 |title=Quenton Nelson becomes No. 9 for 2014 |last=Fortuna |first=Matt |date=May 2, 2013 |website=espn |access-date=April 24, 2018}}</ref> He also supplemented his football and strength trainings with [[Taekwondo]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2083001-freak-notre-dame-recruit-quenton-nelson-destroys-two-boards-with-one-punch |title=Freak Notre Dame Recruit Quenton Nelson Destroys Two Boards with One Punch |date=June 2, 2014 |work=Bleacher Report |access-date=April 24, 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==College career==\nAfter [[redshirt (college sports)|redshirting]] his first year at Notre Dame in 2014, Nelson played in all 12 games and made one start in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.app.com/story/sports/columnists/stephen-edelson/2015/09/29/notre-dame-quenton-nelson-potential/73016792/ |title=Notre Dame's Quenton Nelson flashes his potential |last=Edelson, Stephen |date=September 29, 2015 |website=app.com |access-date=April 24, 2018}}</ref> In 2016, he started all 12 games.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ndinsider.com/football/how-notre-dame-s-quenton-nelson-evolved-into-the-nation/article_9ed601be-be4b-11e7-a7c5-9b5d2199fc17.html |title=How Notre Dame's Quenton Nelson evolved into the nation's most feared offensive lineman |last=Vorel |first=Mike |date=November 1, 2017 |website=ND Insider |access-date=April 24, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://blog.seattlepi.com/seahawksdraftblog/2017/09/21/quenton-nelson-is-tremendous-a-very-early-2018-pick/ |title=Quenton Nelson is tremendous & a very early 2018 pick |last=Staton, Rob |date=September 21, 2017 |website=Seattle pi |access-date=April 24, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nbcsports.com/chicago/notre-dame/quenton-nelson-bringing-mean-streak-notre-dames-ol |title=Quenton Nelson bringing a mean streak to Notre Dame's OL |last=Stankevitz, JJ |date=September 24, 2015 |website=NBC Spots Chicago |access-date=April 24, 2018}}</ref> He was named a unanimous first team All-American after the 2017 season.  On January 8, 2018, Nelson announced that he would forgo his last year of eligibility and enter the [[2018 NFL Draft|draft]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cbssports.com/fantasy/football/news/quenton-nelson-declares-for-draft/ |title=Notre Dame guard Quenton Nelson entering the 2018 draft |date=January 8, 2018 |publisher=CBS Sports |access-date=January 8, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Professional career==\n===NFL Draft===\nAt the conclusion of the pre-draft process, Nelson was projected a top ten selection in the first round by NFL draft experts and scouts. He was ranked as the top offensive linemen prospect in the draft by [[Sports Illustrated]] and NFL analysts [[Daniel Jeremiah]] and [[Mike Mayock]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000909727/article/daniel-jeremiahs-top-50-prospects-for-2018-nfl-draft |title=Daniel Jeremiah's top 50 prospects for 2018 NFL Draft |last=Jeremiah, Daniel |date=April 25, 2018 |website=NFL.com |access-date=September 17, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2018/03/07/nfl-draft-top-prospects-big-board-top-100 |title=The 2018 NFL Draft Big Board, Vol 2 |website=si.com |access-date=September 17, 2018}}</ref>\n{{external media\n| video1 =\n[http://www.nfl.com/videos/nfl-draft/0ap3000000926312/Breaking-down-Quenton-Nelson-s-college-highlights NFL Draft Profile: Quenton Nelson]\n| video2 =\n[http://www.nfl.com/videos/nfl-combine/0ap3000000924557/Quenton-Nelson-s-full-2018-NFL-Scouting-Combine-workout Quenton Nelson's NFL Combine Workout]\n| video3 =\n[http://www.nfl.com/videos/nfl-combine/0ap3000000918423/Mayock-s-No-1-interior-OL-Nelson-puts-up-35-reps-on-bench-press Nelson puts up 35 reps on bench press]\n}}\n{{NFL predraft\n| height ft    = 6\n| height in    = 5\n| weight       = 325\n| dash         = \n| ten split    = \n| twenty split = \n| shuttle      = 4.62\n| cone drill   = 7.65\n| vertical     = 26\u00bd\n| broad ft     = 8\n| broad in     = 9\n| bench        = 35\n| wonderlic    = \n| arm span     = 33\u00be\n| hand span    = 10\u215c\n| note         = All values from [[2018 NFL Draft | NFL Draft]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nfl.com/prospects/quenton-nelson?id=32462018-0002-5599-486f-d1010a40f61a |title=NFL Draft Prospect Profile - Quenton Nelson |date=March 1, 2018 |website=nfl.com |access-date=March 1, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.draftscout.com/ratings/dsprofile.php?pyid=130728&draftyear=2018&genpos=og |title=Notre Dame OG Quenton Nelson : 2018 NFL Draft Scout Player Profile |website=NFLDraftScout.com |access-date=May 12, 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===Indianapolis Colts===\n{{external media\n| video1 =\n[http://www.nfl.com/videos/nfl-draft/0ap3000000928983/Colts-select-Quenton-Nelson-No-6-in-the-2018-NFL-Draft Colts draft Quenton Nelson sixth overall]\n| video2 =\n[http://www.nfl.com/videos/nfl-draft/0ap3000000929259/Jim-Irsay-to-Quenton-Nelson-Andrew-needs-protection Jim Irsay calls Quenton Nelson]\n}}\n====2018 season====\nThe [[Indianapolis Colts]] selected Nelson in the first round (sixth overall) of the [[2018 NFL Draft]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000928980/article/quenton-nelson-selected-by-colts-at-no-6-overall |title=Quenton Nelson selected by Colts at No. 6 overall |last=Patra, Kevin |date=April 26, 2018 |website=NFL.com}}</ref> On May 11, 2018, the Colts signed Nelson to a fully guaranteed four-year, $23.88 million contract, including a signing bonus of $15.45 million.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.spotrac.com/nfl/indianapolis-colts/quenton-nelson-25101/ |title=Spotrac.com: Quenton Nelson contract |website=Spotrac.com |access-date=September 17, 2018}}</ref> On November 1, 2018, Nelson was named the NFL Offensive Rookie of the Month for October, after he was part of an offensive line that hadn't allowed a sack in 156 straight dropbacks and had 200 rushing yards in back-to-back games for first time  in 33 years. Nelson becoming the first guard to ever win the award, and he and [[Darius Leonard]] (who won Defensive Player of the Month in September) became the first teammates to win awards in the same season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://amp.indystar.com/amp/1843859002 |title=Colts' Quenton Nelson named Offensive Rookie of the Month |last=Zak Keefer |date=November 1, 2018 |website=[[IndyStar]] |access-date=November 1, 2018}}</ref> He was named to the Pro Bowl as a rookie and was named first-team All-Pro.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001007645/article/allpro-team-patrick-mahomes-among-2018-highlights |title=All-Pro Team: Donald, Mahomes among highlights |last=Teope, Herbie |date=January 4, 2019 |website=NFL.com}}</ref>\n\n====2019 season====\nIn the 2019 season, Nelson appeared in and started all 16 games for the Colts.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/players/N/NelsQu00/gamelog/2019/ |title=Quenton Nelson 2019 Game Log |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |language=en |access-date=January 29, 2020}}</ref> He played 1,042 snaps, allowing zero sacks and committing just three penalties; he earned a grade of 91.2 from [[Pro Football Focus]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Pro Football Focus: Quenton Nelson (2019)|url= https://www.pff.com/nfl/players/quenton-nelson/12954?season=2019 |access-date=February 22, 2020|website=[[Pro Football Focus]]}}</ref> For the second consecutive season, he was named as a First Team All-Pro and earned a Pro Bowl nomination.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.colts.com/news/quenton-nelson-darius-leonard-2019-nfl-all-pro?campaign=sf:fanshare:facebook |title=Quenton Nelson, Darius Leonard Named To 2019 NFL All-Pro Teams |website=www.colts.com |language=en-US |access-date=January 29, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.colts.com/news/darius-leonard-quenton-nelson-2020-pro-bowl?campaign=sf:fanshare:facebook |title=Darius Leonard, Quenton Nelson Selected To 2020 Pro Bowl |website=www.colts.com |language=en-US |access-date=January 29, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Twitter}}\n*[http://www.und.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/quenton_nelson_913624.html Notre Dame Fighting Irish bio]\n*[https://www.colts.com/team/players-roster/quenton-nelson/ Indianapolis Colts bio]\n\n{{2017 NCAA Division I FBS College Football Consensus All-Americans}}\n{{2018 NFL Draft}}\n{{ColtsFirstPick}}\n{{Indianapolis Colts roster navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nelson, Quenton}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Holmdel Township, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Red Bank Catholic High School alumni]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Monmouth County, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from New Jersey]]\n[[Category:American football offensive guards]]\n[[Category:Notre Dame Fighting Irish football players]]\n[[Category:All-American college football players]]\n[[Category:Indianapolis Colts players]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American football offensive guard}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name                = Quenton Nelson\n| image               = Quenton Nelson.png\n| image_size          = \n| alt                 = \n| caption             = Nelson at the [[2020 Pro Bowl]]\n| current_team        = Indianapolis Colts\n| number              = 56\n| position            = [[Guard (American and Canadian football)|Offensive guard]]\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1996|3|19}}\n| birth_place         = [[Holmdel Township, New Jersey|Holmdel, New Jersey]]\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| height_ft           = 6\n| height_in           = 5\n| weight_lb           = 330\n| high_school         = [[Red Bank Catholic High School|Red Bank Catholic]]<br>([[Red Bank, New Jersey]])\n| college             = [[Notre Dame Fighting Irish football|Notre Dame]]\n| draftyear           = 2018\n| draftround          = 1\n| draftpick           = 6\n| pastteams           = \n* [[Indianapolis Colts]] ({{NFL Year|2018}}\u2013present)\n| status              = Active\n| highlights          =\n* 2\u00d7 [[Pro Bowl]] ([[2019 Pro Bowl|2018]], [[2020 Pro Bowl|2019]])\n* 2\u00d7 First-team [[All-Pro]] ([[2018 All-Pro Team|2018]], [[2019 All-Pro Team|2019]])\n* [[PFWA All-Rookie Team]] ([[PFWA All-Rookie Team#2018|2018]])\n* Unanimous [[All-America]]n ([[2017 College Football All-America Team|2017]])\n* ''[[USA Today]]'' High School All-American ([[2013 USA Today All-USA high school football team|2013]])\n| statleague          = NFL\n| statseason          = 2019\n| statweek            =\n| statlabel1          = Games played\n| statvalue1          = 32\n| statlabel2          = Games started\n| statvalue2          = 32\n| nflnew              = quentonnelson/2560820\n}}\n\n'''Quenton<!--Any addition here requires proper sourcing--> Nelson''' (born March 19, 1996) is an [[American football]] [[Guard (American and Canadian football)|offensive guard]] for the [[Indianapolis Colts]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL). He played [[college football]] at [[Notre Dame Fighting Irish football|Notre Dame]] and was drafted by the Colts in the first round (sixth overall) of the [[2018 NFL Draft]]. In his first two seasons in the league, Nelson was named a first-team [[All-Pro]] selection and voted to the [[Pro Bowl]].\n\n==Early years==\nNelson is the youngest of four children of Craig and Maryellen Nelson, in which she noted Quenton to be a large baby at birth (10lb 10 oz or 4.82kg).<ref>{{Citation |title=Quenton Nelson: The Left Guard YOU Should be Talking About {{!}} NFL Films Presents |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FafC8RvD3b8 |language=en |access-date=December 13, 2019}}</ref> He grew up in [[Holmdel Township, New Jersey]] and attended [[Holmdel High School]] as a freshman before transferring to [[Red Bank Catholic High School]] in [[Red Bank, New Jersey]], where he was an All-Star in basketball as a power forward/center.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nj.com/hssports/blog/football/index.ssf/2013/05/quenton_nelson_of_red_bank_catholic_commits_to_notre_dame.html |title=Notre Dame lands commitment from Quenton Nelson of Red Bank Catholic |last=Lanni |first=Patrick |date=May 2, 2013 |website=[[The Star-Ledger]] |access-date=November 18, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.app.com/story/sports/nfl/2018/04/26/nfl-draft-quenton-nelson-first-round/555608002/ |title=NFL Draft: Colts select Holmdel's Quenton Nelson No. 6 overall |last=Edelson |first=Nelson |date=April 26, 2018 |website=[[Asbury Park Press]] |access-date=August 20, 2018}}</ref> He committed to the [[University of Notre Dame]] to play college football.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2013-05-02/sports/chi-notre-dame-football-quenton-nelson-commits-20130502_1_twitter-account-top-lineman-latest-recruiting-haul |title=Notre Dame football: Quenton Nelson commits |last=Hamilton |first=Brian |date=May 2, 2013 |website=Chicago Tribune |access-date=April 24, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/blog/notre-dame-football/post/_/id/15205/nelson-becomes-no-9-for-2014 |title=Quenton Nelson becomes No. 9 for 2014 |last=Fortuna |first=Matt |date=May 2, 2013 |website=espn |access-date=April 24, 2018}}</ref> He also supplemented his football and strength trainings with [[Taekwondo]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2083001-freak-notre-dame-recruit-quenton-nelson-destroys-two-boards-with-one-punch |title=Freak Notre Dame Recruit Quenton Nelson Destroys Two Boards with One Punch |date=June 2, 2014 |work=Bleacher Report |access-date=April 24, 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==College career==\nAfter [[redshirt (college sports)|redshirting]] his first year at Notre Dame in 2014, Nelson played in all 12 games and made one start in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.app.com/story/sports/columnists/stephen-edelson/2015/09/29/notre-dame-quenton-nelson-potential/73016792/ |title=Notre Dame's Quenton Nelson flashes his potential |last=Edelson, Stephen |date=September 29, 2015 |website=app.com |access-date=April 24, 2018}}</ref> In 2016, he started all 12 games.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ndinsider.com/football/how-notre-dame-s-quenton-nelson-evolved-into-the-nation/article_9ed601be-be4b-11e7-a7c5-9b5d2199fc17.html |title=How Notre Dame's Quenton Nelson evolved into the nation's most feared offensive lineman |last=Vorel |first=Mike |date=November 1, 2017 |website=ND Insider |access-date=April 24, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://blog.seattlepi.com/seahawksdraftblog/2017/09/21/quenton-nelson-is-tremendous-a-very-early-2018-pick/ |title=Quenton Nelson is tremendous & a very early 2018 pick |last=Staton, Rob |date=September 21, 2017 |website=Seattle pi |access-date=April 24, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nbcsports.com/chicago/notre-dame/quenton-nelson-bringing-mean-streak-notre-dames-ol |title=Quenton Nelson bringing a mean streak to Notre Dame's OL |last=Stankevitz, JJ |date=September 24, 2015 |website=NBC Spots Chicago |access-date=April 24, 2018}}</ref> He was named a unanimous first team All-American after the 2017 season.  On January 8, 2018, Nelson announced that he would forgo his last year of eligibility and enter the [[2018 NFL Draft|draft]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cbssports.com/fantasy/football/news/quenton-nelson-declares-for-draft/ |title=Notre Dame guard Quenton Nelson entering the 2018 draft |date=January 8, 2018 |publisher=CBS Sports |access-date=January 8, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Professional career==\n===NFL Draft===\nAt the conclusion of the pre-draft process, Nelson was projected a top ten selection in the first round by NFL draft experts and scouts. He was ranked as the top offensive linemen prospect in the draft by [[Sports Illustrated]] and NFL analysts [[Daniel Jeremiah]] and [[Mike Mayock]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000909727/article/daniel-jeremiahs-top-50-prospects-for-2018-nfl-draft |title=Daniel Jeremiah's top 50 prospects for 2018 NFL Draft |last=Jeremiah, Daniel |date=April 25, 2018 |website=NFL.com |access-date=September 17, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2018/03/07/nfl-draft-top-prospects-big-board-top-100 |title=The 2018 NFL Draft Big Board, Vol 2 |website=si.com |access-date=September 17, 2018}}</ref>\n{{external media\n| video1 =\n[http://www.nfl.com/videos/nfl-draft/0ap3000000926312/Breaking-down-Quenton-Nelson-s-college-highlights NFL Draft Profile: Quenton Nelson]\n| video2 =\n[http://www.nfl.com/videos/nfl-combine/0ap3000000924557/Quenton-Nelson-s-full-2018-NFL-Scouting-Combine-workout Quenton Nelson's NFL Combine Workout]\n| video3 =\n[http://www.nfl.com/videos/nfl-combine/0ap3000000918423/Mayock-s-No-1-interior-OL-Nelson-puts-up-35-reps-on-bench-press Nelson puts up 35 reps on bench press]\n}}\n{{NFL predraft\n| height ft    = 6\n| height in    = 5\n| weight       = 325\n| dash         = \n| ten split    = \n| twenty split = \n| shuttle      = 4.62\n| cone drill   = 7.65\n| vertical     = 26\u00bd\n| broad ft     = 8\n| broad in     = 9\n| bench        = 35\n| wonderlic    = \n| arm span     = 33\u00be\n| hand span    = 10\u215c\n| note         = All values from [[2018 NFL Draft | NFL Draft]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nfl.com/prospects/quenton-nelson?id=32462018-0002-5599-486f-d1010a40f61a |title=NFL Draft Prospect Profile - Quenton Nelson |date=March 1, 2018 |website=nfl.com |access-date=March 1, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.draftscout.com/ratings/dsprofile.php?pyid=130728&draftyear=2018&genpos=og |title=Notre Dame OG Quenton Nelson : 2018 NFL Draft Scout Player Profile |website=NFLDraftScout.com |access-date=May 12, 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===Indianapolis Colts===\n{{external media\n| video1 =\n[http://www.nfl.com/videos/nfl-draft/0ap3000000928983/Colts-select-Quenton-Nelson-No-6-in-the-2018-NFL-Draft Colts draft Quenton Nelson sixth overall]\n| video2 =\n[http://www.nfl.com/videos/nfl-draft/0ap3000000929259/Jim-Irsay-to-Quenton-Nelson-Andrew-needs-protection Jim Irsay calls Quenton Nelson]\n}}\n====2018 season====\nThe [[Indianapolis Colts]] selected Nelson in the first round (sixth overall) of the [[2018 NFL Draft]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000928980/article/quenton-nelson-selected-by-colts-at-no-6-overall |title=Quenton Nelson selected by Colts at No. 6 overall |last=Patra, Kevin |date=April 26, 2018 |website=NFL.com}}</ref> On May 11, 2018, the Colts signed Nelson to a fully guaranteed four-year, $23.88 million contract, including a signing bonus of $15.45 million.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.spotrac.com/nfl/indianapolis-colts/quenton-nelson-25101/ |title=Spotrac.com: Quenton Nelson contract |website=Spotrac.com |access-date=September 17, 2018}}</ref> On November 1, 2018, Nelson was named the NFL Offensive Rookie of the Month for October, after he was part of an offensive line that hadn't allowed a sack in 156 straight dropbacks and had 200 rushing yards in back-to-back games for first time  in 33 years. Nelson becoming the first guard to ever win the award, and he and [[Darius Leonard]] (who won Defensive Player of the Month in September) became the first teammates to win awards in the same season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://amp.indystar.com/amp/1843859002 |title=Colts' Quenton Nelson named Offensive Rookie of the Month |last=Zak Keefer |date=November 1, 2018 |website=[[IndyStar]] |access-date=November 1, 2018}}</ref> He was named to the Pro Bowl as a rookie and was named first-team All-Pro.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001007645/article/allpro-team-patrick-mahomes-among-2018-highlights |title=All-Pro Team: Donald, Mahomes among highlights |last=Teope, Herbie |date=January 4, 2019 |website=NFL.com}}</ref>\n\n====2019 season====\nIn the 2019 season, Nelson appeared in and started all 16 games for the Colts.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/players/N/NelsQu00/gamelog/2019/ |title=Quenton Nelson 2019 Game Log |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |language=en |access-date=January 29, 2020}}</ref> He played 1,042 snaps, allowing zero sacks and committing just three penalties; he earned a grade of 91.2 from [[Pro Football Focus]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Pro Football Focus: Quenton Nelson (2019)|url= https://www.pff.com/nfl/players/quenton-nelson/12954?season=2019 |access-date=February 22, 2020|website=[[Pro Football Focus]]}}</ref> For the second consecutive season, he was named as a First Team All-Pro and earned a Pro Bowl nomination.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.colts.com/news/quenton-nelson-darius-leonard-2019-nfl-all-pro?campaign=sf:fanshare:facebook |title=Quenton Nelson, Darius Leonard Named To 2019 NFL All-Pro Teams |website=www.colts.com |language=en-US |access-date=January 29, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.colts.com/news/darius-leonard-quenton-nelson-2020-pro-bowl?campaign=sf:fanshare:facebook |title=Darius Leonard, Quenton Nelson Selected To 2020 Pro Bowl |website=www.colts.com |language=en-US |access-date=January 29, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Twitter}}\n*[http://www.und.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/quenton_nelson_913624.html Notre Dame Fighting Irish bio]\n*[https://www.colts.com/team/players-roster/quenton-nelson/ Indianapolis Colts bio]\n\n{{2017 NCAA Division I FBS College Football Consensus All-Americans}}\n{{2018 NFL Draft}}\n{{ColtsFirstPick}}\n{{Indianapolis Colts roster navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nelson, Quenton}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\